From 33efb0019ab0705aa5e207fa8e1a7eb5b341d6d2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?S=C3=B6nke=20Liebau?= <soenke.liebau@stackable.tech>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 18:24:04 +0100
Subject: HBASE-XXXXX Add WAL roll trigger based on filesystem sync count

Motivation:
When running HBase on Azure ADLS (Azure Data Lake Storage), each blob
has a hard limit of 50,000 append operations. WAL files are written via
append calls, with each filesystem-level sync constituting one append.
The existing WAL rotation triggers (time-based, size-based, slow-sync)
do not account for this append count limit, which can cause WAL writes
to fail with errors once the limit is exceeded.

Changes:
Add a new configurable WAL rotation trigger that rolls the WAL file
after a specified number of filesystem-level syncs. This is implemented
by tracking syncs via an AtomicInteger counter in AbstractFSWAL that
increments in postSync() (the common chokepoint for both FSHLog and
AsyncFSWAL) and resets to zero on each successful roll.

A new doCheckSyncCount() method is called from FSHLog.checkLogRoll()
and AsyncFSWAL.syncCompleted() alongside the existing size and
slow-sync checks. A new SYNC_COUNT value is added to the
RollRequestReason enum, with corresponding metrics wired through
MetricsWALSource, MetricsWALSourceImpl, and MetricsWAL.

New configuration parameter:
  hbase.regionserver.wal.roll.on.sync.count
    Maximum number of filesystem-level syncs allowed per WAL file
    before triggering a rotation. When the count is reached, a log
    roll is requested with reason SYNC_COUNT. The counter resets to
    zero after each successful roll. Set to 0 (default) to disable.
    Recommended value for ADLS: 40000 (leaving margin below the
    50,000 limit, since other roll triggers may fire first).

New metric:
  syncCountRollRequest
    Counts how many times a WAL roll was requested due to the
    filesystem sync count threshold being reached.

Files changed:
  WALActionsListener.java      - SYNC_COUNT enum value
  MetricsWALSource.java        - metric constant and interface method
  MetricsWALSourceImpl.java    - metric counter implementation
  MetricsWAL.java              - switch case for SYNC_COUNT
  AbstractFSWAL.java           - config, counter, postSync increment,
                                 roll reset, doCheckSyncCount()
  FSHLog.java                  - wired into checkLogRoll()
  AsyncFSWAL.java              - wired into syncCompleted()
  TestMetricsWAL.java          - updated for SYNC_COUNT
  AbstractTestFSWAL.java       - unit tests for threshold logic
  AbstractTestLogRolling.java  - integration test with LogRoller

